PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa addressed the nation on Monday on the progress of the regulations attempting to limit the spread of the COVID-19 virus. The president commended South Africans for, for the most part, responding positively to the regulations of the lockdown. WATCH: President Ramaphosa addresses the nation Ramaphosa announced the number of confirmed COVID-19 cases has risen to 1,326 and the number of deaths has risen to three.  WATCH: Govt update on SA lockdown intervention "I am calling once again on each and every South African to stay at home for the next 17 days. Leave your home if you need to get food and essential provisions or to collect a social grant or to buy medicine or get urgent medical care. "The only people who can go to work, are health workers, security and emergency personnel, those who work to keep our people supplied with food, medicine, and basic goods and other providers of essential services as defined in the regulations," he said. Ramaphosa said the following 17 days will not be easy for anyone, but urged the public to take the precautions seriously and be careful. The president announced a new phase to the management of the COVID-19 pandemic by the government and said 10,000 field workers will be visiting homes to screen people for symptoms of the virus. READ: COVID-19: 21-days lockdown explained An extensive tracing system will be rapidly deployed to trace those who have been in contact with coronavirus positive citizens Ramaphosa thanked the philanthropic donations from Motsepe Foundation for R1-billion, Naspers' donation of R1.5-billion and owner of Japan-based Alibaba, Jack Ma's donation of medical equipment. The president also thanked the frontline and essential workers in the ongoing fight against the virus. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.